
Overview of noun sanction

The noun sanction has 4 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                       
1. (2) sanction, countenance, endorsement, indorsement, warrant, imprimatur -- (formal and explicit approval; "a Democrat usually gets the union's endorsement")
2. (1) sanction -- (a mechanism of social control for enforcing a society's standards)
3. authority, authorization, authorisation, sanction -- (official permission or approval; "authority for the program was renewed several times")
4. sanction -- (the act of final authorization; "it had the sanction of the church")

Overview of verb sanction

The verb sanction has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                       
1. (6) approve, O.K., okay, sanction -- (give sanction to; "I approve of his educational policies")
2. (1) sanction -- (give authority or permission to)
3. sanction -- (give religious sanction to, such as through on oath; "sanctify the marriage")
